    },
    {
      "id": "c07f06a422451731f0e561781b07edd3019f7f5d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 597,
        "name": "Sebastien Buisson",
        "email": "sbuisson@ddn.com",
        "username": "sbuisson"
      },
      "date": "2023-10-27 09:28:53.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nThanks for the patch Gian-Carlo. I think it fixes the problem when Lustre is built from source packages, but breaks the dependency on openssl-devel when built from the source tree.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "93f491f35f416c2c98eaabab67708cd8072066c5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2023-10-27 13:57:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Verified-1\n\nFailed enforced test review-ldiskfs-dne-arm on RHEL 8.8/aarch64, RHEL 8.8/x86_64 uploaded by Trevis Autotest from trevis-108vm11: https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/5a69a1ca-5ba1-4c1f-ae9b-792a3f468ccc ran 5 tests.  1 tests failed: sanity-lnet.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "702dccea79276f92ce8052625d5f2fcf5487e170",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 830,
        "name": "Gian-Carlo DeFazio",
        "email": "defazio1@llnl.gov",
        "username": "defazio1"
      },
      "date": "2023-10-30 15:41:42.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(1 comment)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "fe7a56f402975d863593b6f98c5ba1ed2b96e265",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 597,
        "name": "Sebastien Buisson",
        "email": "sbuisson@ddn.com",
        "username": "sbuisson"
      },
      "date": "2023-11-14 08:21:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI cannot really tell if it is good or bad to have divergent logics when building from source tree and from source package. Maybe someone with more experience in this area can comment?\n\nBut what I can tell is that we really need to avoid failing the build in the middle of the compilation phase. If we do not check for openssl-devel at configure time, we will try to build l_getsepol and fail. This is bad because we wasted time trying to compile whereas we could have checked in advance. And also because when compilation fails, it is not always easy to identify the reason for the failure, as opposed to a clear configure check that says 'openssl-devel is missing'.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "6345b5cf165af0969025819b8add8bd091154afa",
